On 12/24/04 4:51 PM, "Tom Shinn" <turtlebus(-at-)msn.com> wrote:

> Yours is similar to what I was thinking about doing. Why do you recommend
> such a large hole and grommet? I have some 1/2" gromets that have a hole in
> the middle that are just right to fit the cable snug.
> 
> Tom
> 75 bus "Turtlebus"
> 80 Westy "as yet unnamed"


Because if you want to remove the sender at some later time, you need a hole
big enough for the plastic plug, or the ring, to pass through. If you use a
small hole, the sender will be "captive" on the tin, which might be a pain.

